/**
 * hir/errors: HIR-phase exception type documentation.
 *
 * The individual HIR exception types and the HirError group are all defined
 * in src/diagnostics/error.nx. They are listed here for documentation only.
 *
 * HIR-phase exceptions (defined in src/diagnostics/error.nx):
 *   - InvalidSymbolTag — pure HIR ICE (E0001)
 *   - CyclicImport     — cycle detected in the import graph (E4001)
 *   - ImportNotExported — selective import of a non-exported symbol (E4005)
 *   - InImport          — file-context wrapper for errors inside an import
 *   - InTargetFile      — file-context wrapper for errors in the target file
 *   - HirError group   — union of the above + linearity/codegen members
 *
 * Note: individual exception types are kept in src/diagnostics/error.nx (not here)
 * so the seed compiler's wf_throw and constructor-lookup checks can find them
 * in the entry-file's enum_defs. The seed does not reliably register TLException
 * nodes from transitively-imported files.
 */
